<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBarron_LD.2C_Hecht_L.2C_McColl_IH.2C_Blanch_EW2004">Barron LD, Hecht L, McColl IH, Blanch EW (2004). "Raman optical activity comes of age". <i>Molec. Phys.</i> <b>102</b> (8): 731–744. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1080%2F00268970410001704399" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1080%2F00268970410001704399" rel="nofollow">10.1080/00268970410001704399</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Raman+optical+activity+comes+of+age&amp;rft.jtitle=Molec.+Phys.&amp;rft.aulast=Barron+LD%2C+Hecht+L%2C+McColl+IH%2C+Blanch+EW&amp;rft.au=Barron+LD%2C+Hecht+L%2C+McColl+IH%2C+Blanch+EW&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=102&amp;rft.issue=8&amp;rft.pages=731%26ndash%3B744&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1080%2F00268970410001704399&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Raman_spectroscopy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFB._Schrader.2C_G._Bergmann.2C_Fresenius._Z.1967">B. Schrader, G. Bergmann, Fresenius. Z. (1967). <i>Anal. Chem.</i>: 225–230.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.jtitle=Anal.+Chem.&amp;rft.aulast=B.+Schrader%2C+G.+Bergmann%2C+Fresenius.+Z.&amp;rft.au=B.+Schrader%2C+G.+Bergmann%2C+Fresenius.+Z.&amp;rft.date=1967&amp;rft.pages=225%E2%80%93230&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Raman_spectroscopy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFP._Matousek.2C_A._W._Parker2006">P. Matousek, A. W. Parker (2006). "Bulk Raman Analysis of Pharmaceutical Tablets". <i>Applied Spectroscopy</i> <b>60</b>: 1353–1357. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1366%2F000370206779321463" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1366%2F000370206779321463" rel="nofollow">10.1366/000370206779321463</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Bulk+Raman+Analysis+of+Pharmaceutical+Tablets&amp;rft.jtitle=Applied+Spectroscopy&amp;rft.aulast=P.+Matousek%2C+A.+W.+Parker&amp;rft.au=P.+Matousek%2C+A.+W.+Parker&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.volume=60&amp;rft.pages=1353%E2%80%931357&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1366%2F000370206779321463&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Raman_spectroscopy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFP._Matousek.2C_N._Stone2007">P. Matousek, N. Stone (2007). "Prospects for the diagnosis of breast cancer by noninvasive probing of calcifications using transmission Raman spectroscopy". <i>Journal of Biomedical Optics</i> <b>12</b>: 024008. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1117%2F1.2718934" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1117%2F1.2718934" rel="nofollow">10.1117/1.2718934</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Prospects+for+the+diagnosis+of+breast+cancer+by+noninvasive+probing+of+calcifications+using+transmission+Raman+spectroscopy&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Biomedical+Optics&amp;rft.aulast=P.+Matousek%2C+N.+Stone&amp;rft.au=P.+Matousek%2C+N.+Stone&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.volume=12&amp;rft.pages=024008&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1117%2F1.2718934&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Raman_spectroscopy"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Raman_spectroscopy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://witec.de/en/download/Raman/ImagingMicroscopy04.pdf-" class="external text" title="http://witec.de/en/download/Raman/ImagingMicroscopy04.pdf-" rel="nofollow">Chemical Imaging Without Dyeing</a> - Chemical Imaging Without Dyeing</li>
<li><a href="http://www.jobinyvon.com/Raman/Tutorial-Intro" class="external text" title="http://www.jobinyvon.com/Raman/Tutorial-Intro" rel="nofollow">An introduction to Raman spectroscopy</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.andor.com/chemistry/?app=64" class="external text" title="http://www.andor.com/chemistry/?app=64" rel="nofollow">Raman Fundamentals 'What is Raman Spectroscopy?'</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.doitpoms.ac.uk/tlplib/raman/index.php" class="external text" title="http://www.doitpoms.ac.uk/tlplib/raman/index.php" rel="nofollow">DoITPoMS Teaching and Learning Package - Raman Spectroscopy</a> - an introduction, aimed at undergraduate level</li>
<li><a href="http://161.58.205.25/Raman_Spectroscopy/rtr-ramantutorial.php?ss=800" class="external text" title="http://161.58.205.25/Raman_Spectroscopy/rtr-ramantutorial.php?ss=800" rel="nofollow">Raman Spectroscopy Tutorial</a> - A detailed explanation of Raman Spectroscopy including Resonance-Enhanced Raman Scattering and Surface-Enhanced Raman Scattering.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.abc.net.au/rn/science/ss/stories/s1581469.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.abc.net.au/rn/science/ss/stories/s1581469.htm" rel="nofollow">The Science Show, ABC Radio National</a> - Interview with Scientist on NASA funded project to build Raman Spectrometer for the 2009 Mars mission: a cellular phone size device to detect almost any substance known, with commercial &lt;USD$5000 commercial spin-off, prototyped by June 2006.</li>
<li><a href="http://pubs.acs.org/subscribe/journals/ancham/79/i11/pdf/0607feature_griffiths.pdf" class="external text" title="http://pubs.acs.org/subscribe/journals/ancham/79/i11/pdf/0607feature_griffiths.pdf" rel="nofollow">Raman spectroscopy for medical diagnosis</a> from <a href="http://pubs3.acs.org/acs/journals/toc.page?incoden=ancham&amp;indecade=0&amp;involume=79&amp;inissue=11" class="external text" title="http://pubs3.acs.org/acs/journals/toc.page?incoden=ancham&amp;indecade=0&amp;involume=79&amp;inissue=11" rel="nofollow">the June 1, 2007 issue of <i>Analytical Chemistry</i></a></li>
</ul>
